OL,7,FThe director-general said there were no
OL,8,Fplans to implement any further cuts at
OL,9,FRadio Foyle: "We are committed to
OL,10,Fkeeping the three hours of programming,
OL,11,Fwhich is the half-an-hour news
OL,12,Fprogramme and, I think, two other
OL,13,Fprogrammes. The Mark Patterson Show and
OL,14,FThe Sean Coyle Show will both be kept."
OL,16,FHe added: "That is a commitment until
OL,17,Fwe have to keep reviewing things. That
OL,18,Fis a commitment for the next period. We
OL,19,Fhave no plans to go beyond that `
OL,20,Fabsolutely not."
